Set Up the Salesforce Interactions SDK

After the website developer and data aware specialist complete their steps to set up Salesforce Interactions SDK, the Data Cloud admin finishes up the setup.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
	
To configure connections	Data Cloud Admin permission set
Register the website by creating an app of type website in Data Cloud.
In a Salesforce org with Data Cloud provisioned, select Data Cloud Setup.
Select Configurations, and then click Websites & Mobile Apps.
To create a connector, click New.
Enter the app name, and select the connector type.
To rename your app at a later date, click Edit
Upload your schema to Data Cloud.
To select a JSON Event Type schema file from your computer, click Upload Schema in the Schema block.
Confirm that all events and fields are populated, and save your work.
After your schema is uploaded, examine it for accuracy.
To change your schema at any point, click Update Schema. You can only add new events and fields, the schema must retain all previous events and fields.
To update your schema, click Yes, Update.
To view the full schema you uploaded, click View Full Schema.
Share the Content Delivery Network (CDN) URL for the Unified Web SDK and sitemap with the website developer.
Navigate to the Integration Guide section.
Copy the Content Delivery Network Script.
Share the CDN link with your website developer.
After the website developer shares the sitemap with you and the data aware specialist completes their tasks, complete the setup.
On the Website app details page, click Upload Sitemap in the Sitemap section.
Select the saved sitemap.js file that you received from the website developer, and click Open.
Review the sitemap in the Upload Sitemap section, and click Save.

Events from a configured website now flow into Data Cloud data streams and are available for segmentation.
